programme.title: Live NBA: Dallas @ Boston
programme.desc: Boston Celtics v Dallas Mavericks (Tip-off 1.00am). Coverage of the inter-conference clash from TD Garden. Dirk Nowitzki recently set an NBA record when he returned from injury to play his first match of the campaign for the Mavericks, becoming the first player in history to represent the same team in 21 seasons. While his best days are behind him the German is a certainty to be inducted into the Hall of Fame once his career comes to an end, and attention is already turning towards his teammate Luka Doncic, who is being hailed as a future league MVP even though he is only a few months into his rookie season.

programme.title: Live One-Day International Cricket
programme.sub-title: New Zealand v Sri Lanka: Second ODI
programme.desc: New Zealand v Sri Lanka. Coverage of the second one-day international in the three-match series from Bay Oval, Tauranga. New Zealand claimed victory by 36 runs in the only pervious meeting between the sides here in this format in 2016, but the Black Caps have tasted defeat in the other three 50-over matches they have played here, losing to England last February and twice against South Africa in 2014.

programme.title: Live Test Cricket
programme.sub-title: South Africa v Pakistan: Second Test Day Five
programme.desc: South Africa v Pakistan. Coverage of the fifth and final day of the second test in the three-match series from Newlands Cricket Ground in Cape Town. This is the fourth time these nations have faced each other here in this format of the game, and coming into this contest the Proteas have a 100 per cent record. The most recent encounter took place in February 2013, and on that occasion the hosts claimed a four-wicket victory that was largely thanks to the second innings performance of their bowlers. Having dismissed Pakistan for 169 that set a winning target of 181, and despite a shaky start saw the hosts lose the opening wicket with just 10 runs on the board, the total proved to be achievable.(n)

programme.desc: South Africa v Pakistan. Coverage of the fifth and final day of the second test in the three-match series from Newlands Cricket Ground in Cape Town. This is the fourth time these nations have faced each other here in this format of the game, and coming into this contest the Proteas have a 100 per cent record.
